    <note>Ma(2) Dingguo [24701] Based on generational name, chronological logic Guanguo [24702] and Chiguo would be cousins or brothers. I am designating them as brothers. Dingguo was a poet, who traveled to the capital of Liu(2) Yu(12) [24699], ruler of the puppet state of Qi and presented poems that pleased Yu(12), who appointed him to office. He rose to be a Hanlin academician in Yu(12)'s administration. CBD, 3, 1842.</note>
